sh
# Interpreter for 'vpn-switch getenv <var>' command
# Terminal function that displays effective environment variable value
#
# Default value: "sh"
#   Executes commands to show variable value from environment hierarchy
#   Checks .env/local/ first (overrides)
#   Falls back to .env/default/ (defaults)
#   Falls back to .env-templates/ (templates)
#   Shows source location and value
#
# Function behavior:
#   - Searches for variable in hierarchy order
#   - Shows source location (local/default/template)
#   - Outputs first line of variable file (the actual value)
#   - Exits with error if variable not found
#
# Example usage:
#   vpn-switch getenv VPN_SWITCH_BASE
#   vpn-switch getenv VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_wireguard_connect
#
# Advanced - show commands without executing (for debugging):
#   echo "cat" > .env/local/VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_getenv
#   vpn-switch getenv TEST_VAR                # Show commands only
#
# See ARCHITECTURE.md for details on the environment hierarchy system
